Billing in Azure subscriptions is based on resource usage such as compute hours, storage consumption, and network traffic. Each subscription generates its own billing report.

Organizations can track costs using tools like Azure Cost Management and set budgets and alerts to control spending.

For example, a company can allocate a monthly budget for its development subscription and receive alerts when usage approaches the limit.

A real-life use case is cost optimization in startups. By monitoring billing data, startups can identify unused resources and shut them down to save money.

Another example is enterprise financial reporting, where each department’s cloud usage is tracked separately for accountability.

Effective billing management ensures financial discipline and avoids unexpected costs.
